## 1. Purpose

This guide explains how to begin using the OPRMT™ Framework Repository.

It is designed for readers, contributors, maintainers, prompt engineers, documentation reviewers, and approved implementation partners who need a structured starting point.

This guide does not replace the official OPRMT™ Framework Standard, license, notice, or governance documents.

---

## 2. What This Repository Contains

The OPRMT™ Framework Repository is a structured documentation and governance system for the OPRMT™ Framework and related materials.

The repository may include:

- Official framework standards
- Component-level specifications
- Prompt templates
- Prompt cluster structures
- Prompt Compliance Engineering materials
- DOAS™ scoring references
- Certification support materials
- Repository governance files
- Legal and usage guidance
- Automation scripts
- GitHub issue templates
- GitHub workflow files

---

## 3. Core Framework Structure

OPRMT™ uses five controlled components:

```text
O — Objective
P — Parameters
R — Results
M — Method
T — Tools
```

Each structured prompt or framework document should preserve this order unless a controlled standard change has been approved.

