## 14. Pull Request Process

Use the repository pull request template:

```text
.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md
```

Before opening a pull request:

- Confirm Markdown renders correctly.
- Confirm links are accurate.
- Confirm filenames and paths are correct.
- Confirm ownership notices remain intact.
- Confirm no unsupported claims were introduced.
- Confirm controlled standard changes are linked to a standard change request.
- Confirm related documentation indexes are updated.

---

## 15. Versioning Basics

Recommended version format:

```text
vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
```

Use:

```text
v1.0.0
```

For the first stable public structure.

Version meaning:

| Version Type | Use Case |
|---|---|
| Patch | Typo fixes, link fixes, formatting corrections |
| Minor | New documentation, expanded guidance, non-breaking clarification |
| Major | Structural changes, definition changes, compatibility-impacting updates |

